---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import fs from "node:fs";
import yaml from "js-yaml";

const homepage = yaml.load(
  fs.readFileSync("src/content/homepage/index.yaml", "utf-8")
);
---
<Base path="/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Intensive Outpatient Program &middot; Houston, TX</p>
       <h1 set:html={homepage.heroHeadline}></h1>
        <p class="lead" set:html={homepage.heroSubheadline}></p>
        <p class="sub" set:html={homepage.introText}></p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start the conversation</a>
          <a href="/how-it-works" class="btn btn-ghost">See how it works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="trajectory" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 420 360" role="img">
          <path class="path-bg" d="M28,320 C150,312 188,196 236,138 C282,82 332,60 392,40" />
          <path class="path-line" id="traj" d="M28,320 C150,312 188,196 236,138 C282,82 332,60 392,40" />
          <g class="node"><circle cx="28" cy="320" r="6"></circle><text x="44" y="316" class="lab">Lift-Off</text><text x="44" y="334" class="meta">Weeks 1&ndash;2</text></g>
          <g class="node"><circle cx="236" cy="138" r="6"></circle><text x="252" y="134" class="lab">Ascent</text><text x="252" y="152" class="meta">Weeks 3&ndash;8</text></g>
          <g class="node"><circle cx="392" cy="40" r="6"></circle><text x="300" y="30" class="lab">Orbit</text><text x="300" y="48" class="meta">Weeks 9&ndash;12</text></g>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="band"><div class="wrap"><p>Launch IOP is an <em>intensive outpatient program in Houston, Texas</em>, for young adults experiencing failure-to-launch patterns.</p></div></div>

  <section id="about">
    <div class="wrap reveal">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">When the next step feels out of reach</p>
        <h2>What <em>failure to launch</em> really means</h2>
        <p>It isn't laziness, and it isn't a character flaw. It's a pattern where a capable young adult struggles to move into the milestones of independent life &mdash; and it responds remarkably well to the right structure and support.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stuck-grid">
        <p class="stuck-lead">Often layered with anxiety, depression, or avoidance, it shows up as withdrawal from school, work, and relationships. Recognizing it as a pattern &mdash; rather than a flaw &mdash; is the first step toward changing it.</p>
        <ul class="signs">
          <li><span class="n">i</span> Stalled in school, work, or daily routines</li>
          <li><span class="n">ii</span> Avoidance of responsibilities and social situations</li>
          <li><span class="n">iii</span> Reliance on family for structure and motivation</li>
          <li><span class="n">iv</span> Difficulty with planning and follow-through</li>
          <li><span class="n">v</span> Growing tension and worry at home</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rule-top">
    <div class="wrap reveal">
      <div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Where this leads</p><h2>What participants build at Launch</h2></div>
      <div class="outcomes">
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">i</div><h3>Re-engagement</h3><p>Return to school, work, and community with steady momentum.</p></div>
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">ii</div><h3>Daily structure</h3><p>Stronger executive function &mdash; planning, follow-through, and routine.</p></div>
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">iii</div><h3>Social confidence</h3><p>Emotional resilience and the ability to face, not avoid, hard moments.</p></div>
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">iv</div><h3>Independence</h3><p>Practical living skills that reduce dependence on family.</p></div>
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">v</div><h3>Calmer home life</h3><p>Less tension through clearer boundaries and communication.</p></div>
        <div class="outcome"><div class="num">vi</div><h3>Action over avoidance</h3><p>A repeatable way to move from stuck to meaningful action.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rule-top">
    <div class="wrap reveal">
      <div class="section-head center"><p class="eyebrow">Our framework</p><h2>The pillars of Launch &mdash; <em>REACH</em></h2></div>
      <div class="reach">
        <div class="pillar"><div class="letter">R</div><div class="word">Resilience</div><div class="desc">Recover from setbacks</div></div>
        <div class="pillar"><div class="letter">E</div><div class="word">Engagement</div><div class="desc">Re-enter daily life</div></div>
        <div class="pillar"><div class="letter">A</div><div class="word">Autonomy</div><div class="desc">Act independently</div></div>
        <div class="pillar"><div class="letter">C</div><div class="word">Connection</div><div class="desc">Build relationships</div></div>
        <div class="pillar"><div class="letter">H</div><div class="word">Health</div><div class="desc">Care for mind &amp; body</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-final">
    <div class="wrap cta-grid reveal">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--taupe)">Get started</p>
        <h2>Ready to take the <em>first step?</em></h2>
        <p>Call or send a note and our intake coordinator will reach out. Clinicians referring a client are welcome too.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-light" style="margin-top:12px;">Get in touch</a>
      </div>
      <div class="contact-card">
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Phone</div><a href="tel:7134821590">713-482-1590</a></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Email</div><a href="mailto:info@launchiop.com">info@launchiop.com</a></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Visit</div><a href="https://maps.google.com/?q=4646+Wild+Indigo+Street+Suite+150+Houston+TX+77027" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="line-height:1.5;">4646 Wild Indigo Street, Suite 150<br>Houston, TX 77027</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
